💻 Web Developer Profile

Web Developer committed to enhancing the user journey, optimizing user flow, and leading the design and development of user portals and integrations. Willing to lead by example and actively participate in all coding and debugging efforts. Continuously evaluating product strengths and addressing limitations to drive improvement.

Experienced in road mapping, project planning, and taking ownership of delivery milestones. Actively engaged in project management as the team executes strategic plans. Previous responsibilities include communicating progress and status updates to stakeholders.

🌐 Project Highlight

This website was built using{" "} NodeJS {" "} featuring asynchronous programming, modular architecture, and React libraries for dynamic component rendering.{" "}

🚀 Technical Interests

My passion for web applications and technology centers around the three core languages of the web:

  • HTML – The standard markup language for structuring content in the browser
  • CSS – The style sheet language that defines the visual presentation of HTML elements
  • JavaScript – A powerful and versatile language that drives interactivity and functionality across modern web applications

Hyper Text Markup Language (HTML) & Cascading Style Sheets (CSS)

My strengths: HTML, being the standard markup language for displaying documents in a browser along with CSS the Style Sheet Language for that describes how HTML elements should be displayed.


JavaScript (JS)

The power behind so many web applications a great versatile language.


🧰 Frameworks & Tools

  • Bootstrap
  • jQuery
  • React – Currently the most popular JavaScript library for building user interfaces

⚙️ Runtime Environment

Experienced in refactoring and styling Node.js applications, including the creation and customization of reusable components.
